103 in any such civil action as to any evidence or other matters produced or presented during
104 the proceedings or activities of the committee or as to the findings, recommendations,
105 evaluations, opinions, or other actions of such committee or any members thereof.
106 31-7-33.
107 (a) A hospital shall annually report to the department, and the department shall include as
108 a confidential addendum to the annual hospital questionnaire, the following information:
109 (1) Whether the hospital's governing body has adopted a nurse services staffing plan as
110 required by Code Section 31-7-31;
111 (2) Whether the hospital has established a nurse staffing committee as required by Code
112 Section 31-7-32 that meets the membership requirements of such Code section;
113 (3) Whether the nurse staffing committee has evaluated the hospital's nurse services
114 staffing plan as required by Code Section 31-7-32 and has reported the results of the
115 evaluation to the hospital's governing body as provided by such Code section; and
